data.title: baby face
data.meta_description: BABY FACE meaning: 1. a round, young-looking face:  2. a round, young-looking face: . Learn more.
data.text:
noun [ C ]

(also baby-face, babyface) us/ˈbeɪ.bi ˌfeɪs/ uk/ˈbeɪ.bi ˌfeɪs/

More examplesFewer examples

His baby face was all over billboards and TV commercials.

I would like a chiseled jaw and designer stubble, but I have a baby face and smooth cheeks.

These young teachers have baby faces and are sometimes confused with teenagers on campus.

Despite his baby-face looks and broad grin, he is no stranger to hardball politics.

There he was with his smiling babyface.
